<p>GDP growth: 4.0% GDP: $267bn (PPP: $417bn) Inflation: 4.5% Population: 103.8m GDP per head: $2,570 (PPP: $4,020)</p>

<p>The president, Benigno Aquino, enters the third year of a six-year term with a solid mandate and a loyal lower chamber, but his ratings are sliding and his opponents from the previous regime are resisting investigations into alleged corruption on their watch. Add to this the pressures imposed by festering communist and separatist rebellions and a power-hungry army, and Mr Aquino faces a turbulent year. Slower US growth will weigh on the economy.</p>

